{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> θερᾰπ-εία</b>, <br /> <i>Ionic dialect</i> <b>θερᾰπ-ηΐη</b> (θερᾰπ-είη [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἄρθρων ἐμβολῆς” 80, +others)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], ἡ, <b>service, attendance</b>: <br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> of persons, θ. τῶν θεῶν <b>service paid</b> to the gods, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Euthyphro” 13d, compare 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Electra” 744 (Lyric poetry); θεῶν καὶ ἡρώων θεραπεῖαι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 427b, etc.; ἡ περὶ τοὺς θεοὺς θ. 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 11.24 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀγυιάτιδες θ. <b>worship</b> of Apollo Agyieus, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 187; τὴν θ. ἀποδιδόναι τοῖς θεοῖς 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1329a32; θ. τῆς μήνιδος 4th c.AD: Julianus Imperator “Orationes” 5.159b: _absolutely_, πᾶσαν θ. ὡς ἰσόθεος θεραπευόμενος 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 255a, compare 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 4.2.4 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of parents, γονέων θεραπείας καὶ τιμάς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 886c, compare 5th c.BC: Gorgias Rhetor et Sophista “fragment” 6 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of children, <b>nurture, care</b>, μικροὺς παῖδας θεραπείας δεομένους [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 13.45; θ. καὶ ἐσθής 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 3.11.4 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; θ. σώματος, ψυχῆς, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 464b, “La.” 185e. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.2</b></Level3> <b>service done to gain favour, paying court</b>, θ. τοῦ κοινοῦ καὶ τῶν αἰεὶ προεστώτων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.11; ἐν θεραπείᾳ ἔχειν πολλῇ [prev. author] 1.55; πάσῃ θεραπείᾳ θεραπεύειν τινά